<TEXT>
milanese breathed easier and turned to 
unusual means of transportation after authorities ordered a oneday 
ban on private cars 
bicycles skateboards and roller skates replaced cars on the 
streets of italys business capital on sunday as private traffic 
was banned between 930 am and 630 pm to combat air pollution 
the regions 300 electric car owners met downtown with their 
vehicles while part of the police went on horseback 
authorities in the city of 3 million people doubled the number 
of buses and streetcars and tripled the number of subway trains 
usually in use on sundays 
i think the citizens took it well mayor paolo pillitteri 
told reporters maybe a sunday spent differently will make people 
think about whats happening to our city 
it was the longest ban on cars in italy since driving was 
forbidden throughout the country on holidays at the height of the 
oil crisis in 1973 
dry windless weather has increased air pollution across 
northern italy in the most polluted areas of milan carbon 
monoxide readings reached dangerous levels on saturday 
city officials said they might repeat sundays ban or take other 
measures if air pollution remains at alarming levels 
</TEXT>
