<TEXT>
a chartered fishing boat with nine people 
aboard capsized and broke up in 15foot swells in a rivers mouth 
sunday leaving one person dead and six people missing coast guard 
officials said 
the 45foot gambler capsized around 4 pm while crossing a 
sandbar in the mouth of the quillayute river as it headed for the 
harbor of this village by the pacific ocean the coast guard said 
a coast guard helicopter plucked three people from the water 
but one was dead on arrival at forks community hospital officials 
said 
jerry wilson and ron wilson both in their 20s and both of 
aberdeen were listed in stable condition at the hospital said 
hospital nursing supervisor barbara enos 
the name of the person who died was not released pending 
notification of relatives 
a 44foot coast guard motor lifeboat from lapush searched 
through heavy fog sunday night for possible survivors or bodies in 
the water chief petty officer dave edwards said in a telephone 
interview from the quillayute river coast guard station 
the helicopter also searched but returned to port angeles 80 
miles east of lapush after running low on fuel 
the clallam county sheriffs office sent a 10member search and 
rescue team to lapush to search the beach said sheriffs 
communications officer bill logan 
the entrance to lapushs harbor is a narrow waterway at the 
mouth of the quillayute 
the gambler was from tacoma but has been moored lately in 
lapush edwards said 
