<DOCNO> AP900122-0011 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
the dome of his former haunt the us 
capitol looms seven miles up the potomac river as lowell weicker 
his 6foot5inch frame a little thinner than when he patrolled the 
senate ponders returning to politics 
weicker the nixon antagonist and maverick republican from 
connecticut has dropped off the radar screen of politics in the 
year since his upset loss to democrat joseph lieberman 
he has been quietly building a public outreach group research 
america an association of universities hospitals and 
philanthropies devoted to promoting biomedical research where his 
job is to sell the priority of biomedical research to the 
american people in the same way you sell a hamburger or a can of 
beer 
but the 58yearold millionaire says he misses the political 
battlefield and is considering a run for governor of connecticut 
one could compare research america to elba if one wanted 
to said dick foley the connecticut gop chief and no supporter 
of weicker referring to the island where napoleon was exiled 
weicker says he never wanted to use research america as a 
platform for political selfpromotion but as he considers 
returning to politics the organization is preparing a media blitz 
featuring weicker that will promote research for cures for such 
diseases as multiple sclerosis and cystic fibrosis 
weicker closes out each of the tv ads by saying to me its 
outrageous that a country as prosperous as america doesnt spend 
more on medical research 
the organization has a 1 million budget this year and hopes to 
triple that figure within three years through contributions from 
its member organizations 
the big part of our budget is going to be advertising 
weicker says 
in the meantime weicker says he misses the political fray and 
predicts he could win the states top office but he is also 
realistic 
the last time i asked connecticut how am i doing i didnt 
get a very good answer weicker said 
the speculation about weicker has been fueled by the absence of 
any declared candidates of statewide stature incumbent democratic 
gov william oneill has yet to decide whether he wants another 
term and other potential contenders are either regional 
politicians or businessmen 
weicker who inherited a fortune from his grandfathers 
pharmaceutical business says he could easily stay where he is he 
spends more time with his family has a nice view of the potomac 
and doesnt have to attend late night senate sessions in fact he 
has hardly been on capitol hill since losing his seat 
when i accepted the job for research america i made it very 
clear that i would not lobby period weicker said when i was 
in the senate i used to really look with disdain on my 
excolleagues who used to lurk in the dining room and gymnasium and 
the halls doing their thing 
even if he did lobby the senate weicker wonders whether he 
would have much impact his outspoken often undiplomatic style 
which first gained prominence during the watergate hearings when he 
lambasted president nixon for what he viewed as that 
administrations abuse of the constitution frequently earned him 
