the events of the past few days have been the most difficult 
of my life more difficult than fighting my way out of poverty as 
black youth born in the segregated deep south more difficult than 
the fear and hatred i faced as a civil rights leader in the 1960s 
more difficult than i could have imagined 
because this time i have come face to face with my deepest 
