the us role should be in encouraging and aiding those emerging 
new democracies as they struggle with economic stagnation almost 
certainly there will be a political consensus that some kind of aid 
should be extended as there was last year on aiding poland and 
hungary 
the real question will boil down to the availability of funds 
and what kind of agreement will be reached between the 
administration and congress said rep dante fascell dfla 
chairman of the house foreign affairs committee 
bush has renewed his nonewtaxes vow for this year meaning any 
money for newly eligible recipients in eastern europe and panama 
will have to be found by cutting current programs the aid budget 
is already so tight that some us friends and allies may come away 
emptyhanded 
