<TEXT>
supreme court justice sandra day oconnor 
sometimes seems to be shaking her head involuntarily from the 
bench and although other people have noticed and mentioned it to 
her she says she is not aware of it 
court spokeswoman toni house said oconnor has not seen a doctor 
about it and she certainly in no way believes it impedes her 
ability to do her job 
attorneys and others attending the courts oral argument 
sessions first noticed oconnors headshaking in 1985 it seems to 
have become more pronounced in recent months 
the justice answered through her spokeswoman several questions 
posed to her by the associated press about the matter 
she has never had it diagnosed she is not personally aware of 
any such headshaking but she has had people tell her so ms 
house said 
the shaking while not constant is noticeable when it does 
occur it is an upanddown motion similar to that made by someone 
nodding in the affirmative 
when asked about the shaking in 1986 oconnor said simply that 
she was unaware of it 
