president bush will end a long stalemate with 
congress over who should run the national transportation safety 
board when he nominates james kolstad as chairman a white house 
official said 
bush will make the nomination today charles g untermeyer 
director of presidential personnel told the associated press on 
sunday 
kolstad a former vice president for public relations of 
frontier airlines has been acting chairman of the ntsb since aug 
14 1988 when jim burnett failed to win senate approval for a 
fourth twoyear term as chairman 
the agency has been struggling with a shrinking investigative 
staff and a tight budget as it tries to fulfill its mandate to 
learn the causes of the nations worst accidents in the air sea 
and on land 
one board member joseph tribbe nall was killed nov 28 in a 
plane crash in caracas venezuela where he had gone to give a 
speech 
