introduction of virginia slims and its competitors in 1986 lung 
cancer surpassed breast cancer as the most prevalent cancer in 
women 
one of the things we felt clearly was this the uptown 
campaign was a replication of a marketing strategy they had 
success with in selling cigarettes to women sutton said 
unlike the uptown protest sutton said womens groups didnt 
oppose virginia slims in part because philip morris underwrote many 
womens activities particularly sports 
the tobacco industry has been vying for the loyalties of smaller 
and smaller segments of a shrinking smoking public by offering 
specialized brands 
reynolds premier a smokeless cigarette that produced few 
ashes failed in test markets in 1989 after some smokers complained 
it had a peculiar taste and aroma 
philip morris later introduced superslims a cigarette the 
company says emits 70 percent less smoke 
with its uptown campaign reynolds ran a risk of reawakening the 
lingering desires to ban all cigarette advertising said jack 
trout a partner in trout amp ries greenwich connbased marketing 
consultants 
for the few tiny dollars they are going to pick up by 
penetrating the black market they are going to enrage everyone 
it just gives ammunition to the antis trout said shortly before 
reynolds canceled the test market 
