a civil right it is a privilege granted by the church to those who 
meet its established standards 
the two congregations hope the gay ministers can bring many 
homosexuals back to the flock among other things the three 
endorsed the concept of gay marriages 
their saturday ordinations along with that of a new jersey 
episcopal pastor last month with an acknowledged male mate 
represent a historic foothold in mainstream christianity by 
homosexuals whose sexual orientation generally has been tolerated 
only if it wasnt consummated 
the elca formed two years ago by the merger of three lutheran 
groups bans ordination of selfavowed practicing homosexuals 
it is the largest american lutheran denomination lutherans in 
several northern european countries allow ordination of practicing 
homosexuals 
at the request of sierrapacific synod bishop lyle miller a 
disciplinary committee will consider punitive action against the 
congregations the parishes could be censured suspended 
permanently removed from the church organization or exonerated 
the rev james delange of st francis said his congregation felt 
that to deny the pastoral ministry of a lesbian couple is akin to 
denying a black congregation the right to call a black pastor up 
to 100000 gays and lesbians live within a mile of the centuryold 
church 
we decided that punishment even expulsion is a risk we would 
run for the sake of whats right delange said 
zillhart and frost a couple who studied together at luther 
northwestern seminary and johnson who graduated last year from 
pacific lutheran seminary in berkeley calif also will manage an 
outreach program for northern california homosexuals 
george cooper a 52yearold former roman catholic priest who 
