declaring india will make no deals over 
human corpses prime minister vp singh rejected a 470 million 
settlement with union carbide in the bhopal gas disaster and vowed 
to pursue 3 billion instead 
the new prime minister also said sunday that his government 
would press criminal charges in the case 
the 1984 gas leak the worlds deadliest industrial disaster 
killed more than 3500 people the 470 million settlement was 
accepted last year by the indian supreme court and by singhs 
predecessor rajiv gandhi 
singh was greeted sunday by surging crowds when he arrived at 
