the supreme court declared dec 22 that the gandhi government 
did indeed have the right to be the claimants only 
representative 
the second challenge is still pending and the singh government 
announced jan 12 it would support the challengers 
union carbide has maintained the gas leak was the result of 
sabotage by a disgruntled employee at the bhopal plant the 
government maintained the disaster was caused by company negligence 
methyl isocyanate a liquid used in making pesticides leaked 
from a tank and turned into a deadly vapor when it hit the air dec 
3 1984 while most people were asleep 
according to figures compiled by the government of madhya 
pradesh state which includes bhopal the death toll has reached 
3598 about half the victims died immediately or within a few days 
of exposure to the gas the others died later of respiratory and 
other problems caused by the gas according to government records 
