partys position said david osteen executive director of the 
antiabortion group of course the republican party contains and 
is big enough to contain people with both points of view as is the 
democratic party 
earlier backers of legal abortion raised the specter of 
romanias former communist repression in warning against a rollback 
of abortion rights 
the head of the national abortion rights action league told a 
gathering on capitol hill that legalizing abortions was one of the 
first steps romania took after overthrowing its hated dictator last 
month 
romanians know firsthand what most americans can only imagine 
the deadly impact of government bans on abortion said kate 
michelman executive director of the abortionrights lobbying group 
it would be a travesty if the united states the beacon of 
democracy in the world applauded romanias reforms while adopting 
repressive antichoice laws here at home she said 
activists on both sides of the issue sensing 1990 will be a 
pivotal year in the political debate on abortion held competing 
events marking the anniversary of the high court decision that 
legalized abortions 
abortion foes expected tens of thousands of marchers in 
washington and more at smaller events around the country 
abortionrights advocates also gathered on the mall outside the 
capitol where a temporary memorial was erected in tribute to all 
women who have died from illegal botched abortions including 
becky bell a 17yearold indianapolis girl who died in september 
1988 after a selfinduced abortion 
bill bell her father said his daughter died because indiana 
law requires minors to obtain parental consent before they can get 
a legal abortion 
our daughter was punished he said she was denied a 
reasonable and safe choice because she loved her parents and died 
not wanting to disappoint them how many more young women will 
share beckys fate if we allow our government to deny them a safe 
choice 
sen bob packwood of oregon a leading republican supporter of 
abortion rights said his party is being damaged by the strongly 
antiabortion platform and position of bush who vetoed 
abortionrights bills passed by congress last fall 
he predicted the antiabortion plank in the republican party 
platform will be removed in 1992 
activists on both sides of the abortion issue rallied sunday in 
cities across the country from albany ny to sacramento calif 
leaders of the antiabortion movement planned to meet with 
bushs chief of staff john sununu and other administration 
officials but there were no plans for the president to see them 
white house spokesman marlin fitzwater said friday sununu is a 
strong opponent of abortion 
others planning to speak to the antiabortion rally included 
republican sens jesse helms of north carolina and gordon humphrey 
of new hampshire 
abortion opponents have held their march for life every year 
since the courts decision 
but this years events had a new significance it was the first 
since the high courts webster decision in july 1989 which opened 
the door for states to impose some restrictions on abortion 
most of the time this is a sad occasion said nancy myers 
spokeswoman for the national right to life committee but theres 
a sense of hope this year because for the first time since 1973 the 
supreme court has said it will allow some reasonable limits on 
abortion 
the march came as political debate on abortion has intensified 
abortion opponents have said they intend to push for new 
restrictions on abortions in many state legislatures but 
candidates who supported abortion rights won key elections last 
fall and prochoice leaders claim public opinion has shifted to 
their side 
