<TEXT>
demonstrators carried the battle for the hearts and minds of 
americans on the abortion issue to state capitals today to 
commemorate the 17th anniversary of the supreme courts roe vs 
wade ruling 
the demonstrations began sunday when an estimated 25000 to 
30000 people joined dueling rallies in phoenix while supporters 
of legalized abortion sang and chanted in albany ny and 
opponents held baby showers for poor women who choose to have 
children in provo utah 
demonstrations also were held in boston raleigh nc and 
spokane wash 
today there were rallies by both sides in washington dc by 
antiabortion groups in trenton nj and salt lake city and by a 
prochoice group in baton rouge la in indianapolis bells tolled 
at a a dozen churches to mark the day rung 25 times one time for 
every million babies killed since 1973 said right to life 
spokeswoman kathleen porter 
in baton rouge the newly formed coalition for reproductive 
freedom wound a 200foot ribbon around the state capitol steps as a 
symbol of their support for roe vs wade 
in trenton about 150 protesters marched in front of the new 
jersey statehouse the site of recent debates over a bill to 
require notification of parents whose minor daughters seek 
abortions a similar protest at the utah capitol also drew about 
150 abortion opponents 
