<TEXT>
world chess champion garri kasparov on monday 
condemned the storming of his native city of baku by soviet troops 
saying too much force was used and it came too late to save the 
armenians 
kasparov who is of armenian and jewish descent and once wrote 
that his roots were in moslem capital of azerbaijan volunteered to 
mediate the ethnic dispute which he said could spread and lead to 
a bloodbath across the soviet union 
at a moscow news conference marked by an evenhandedness seldom 
seen in the twoyear armenianazerbaijani conflict kasparov said 
there were plenty of interior ministry troops and police in baku 
before saturdays attack yet they took no armed action against the 
roving squads who reportedly killed at least 67 armenians and 
ravaged 1200 apartments in a sixday campaign of terror 
instead of halting the murderers officials evacuated the 
armenians and kasparov contended virtually all had left by the 
time soviet troops attacked on saturday 
that is why i cannot accept the official explanation that 
the troops attacked baku to stop the ethnic violence he said 
kasparov said he thought the attack was meant to crush the 
proindependence movement in azerbaijan and warn similar groups in 
other republics 
i fear that what is now happening in azerbaijan may lead to a 
terrible bloodbath in the whole country said kasparov 26 he 
added that he fears angry azerbaijanis could turn on the 100000 
russian residents of baku expanding the ethnic conflict 
if clashes are provoked between russians and azerbaijanis and 
if there are victims or refugees among the russian population just 
think what might happen if they show up in moscow he said 
baku like many soviet cities is home to a variety of ethnic 
groups in his autobiography child of change kasparov wrote 
about his boyhood experiences in the azerbaijani capital my 
roots are in baku that knowledge gives me strength when i go off 
to conquer other worlds and gives me solace when i return 
kasparov spends most of his time now in moscow where he has a 
russian wife 
at least 167 people have been killed since the wave of violence 
began 10 days ago including 95 since soviet troops poured into the 
city saturday morning and were met by firebombs and machinegun 
fire azerbaijanis estimate the death toll is far higher and 
kasparov put it at 500 to 600 
kasparov who rescued 60 of his friends and relatives wednesday 
night said the government has shown it is either unwilling or 
unable to solve the armeniaazerbaijan dispute and called for 
individuals to begin direct negotiations between the neighboring 
republics he offered to act as a mediator 
he declined to lay blame exclusively on president mikhail s 
gorbachev during the news conference but in an interview with the 
spanish newspaper el pais he said the violence was cultivated by 
conservatives to undermine gorbachev and he blamed the soviet 
leader for not taking decisive action 
kasparov who became the youngest world chess champion in 
november 1985 and earlier this month became the highest rated 
player in history has spoken out frequently on domestic problems 
in the soviet union 
he said he used his own money to charter a plane virtually 
impossible in the soviet union with the help of the chess union 
he managed to get his refugees past azerbaijani mobs to the baku 
airport on a back road and 40 of them are staying with him in 
moscow 
in a telephone interview with the associated press kasparovs 
wife maria said the passengers included two of his mothers 
brothers other relatives several of his chess friends and eight 
to 10 strangers who happened to be at the baku airport 
azerbaijani friends helped his group escape kasparov said and 
he expressed sympathy for innocent azerbaijanis killed when the 
troops attacked 
kasparov also blamed the troops themselves for arming both the 
armenian and azerbaijani extremists 
tass reported that militants obtained helicopters tanks and 
even groundtoground missiles armenian activists carried one of 
their fallen leaders to his grave sunday in an armored personnel 
carrier 
my impression is the population of baku would have favored a 
radical and stronghanded curtailment of the repressions against 
the armenian population he said nonetheless the pogroms and 
repressions went on in full view and silent consent of the militia 
and interior troops 
kasparov also criticized authorities for ignoring the 
explosive problem of 160000 homeless and jobless azerbaijani 
refugees from armenia who have been waiting in baku for 
resettlement for as long as two years 
he specifically blamed the killings on the desperation of the 
refugees who terorized the armenian population of baku to grab 
their apartments when they fled a program to find them jobs and 
apartments failed in august 1988 he said 
you do not have to be a politician or a particularly 
farsighted person to see the political danger that lies in 
homeless people who have nothing to look forward to he said 
i lost two relatives in baku so i have serious reasons to cry 
and to shout he said but i dont think it will help i dont 
want to see another 100000 killed its suicide to continue 
no matter what happens the two republics will forever border 
one another no matter how long the war may last sooner or later 
they will have to start negotiations for peace he said 
he suggested that armenians abroad especially in the united 
states and france should work with moslem groups in saudi arabia 
and turkey which must naturally be interested in a peaceful 
solution to this conflict 
