widely expected to be out of prison mandela along with sisulu and 
other recently freed colleagues should give the organization a 
highprofile authoritative voice inside the country 
the government considers the older anc leaders more moderate and 
would prefer to negotiate with them rather than the young lions 
should the two sides end up at the same conference table there 
appears to be little chance of a quick breakthrough 
the anc seeks a oneperson onevote democracy which de klerk 
opposes saying it will lead to black domination of the nations 5 
million whites he envisions powersharing with blacks but with 
whites having some sort of veto power on major policy issues 
