democratic gov rose moffords decision not to 
run for office this fall announced after weeks of conflicting 
signals has thrown arizona politics and government for a loop 
mrs mofford said she had no idea who might run in her place 
and would not say who she favored 
but with four republicans including impeached gov evan mecham 
already in the race and control of the statehouse during a 
redistricting year at stake the names of a halfdozen democrats 
were being mentioned as possible candidates before mrs mofford had 
finished speaking thursday 
