sexual act in the car bock said a resolution to the bill will 
urge newspapers to print the names of people found guilty of 
engaging in prostitution 
its a common thing for these men to drive by pick up a 
prostitute drive around the corner have sex and then drop her 
off ms gooden said a lot of the activity has been going on 
in the cars 
ms gooden said she doesnt believe the bill will stop 
prostitution but it would cause them the johns to have to 
explain why their cars arent there 
a similar bill in portland ore drew criticism from the oregon 
american civil liberties union 
the seizure takes place at the sole discretion of the police 
officer said stevie remington executive director of the oregon 
aclu thats a violation of due process 
portland police department spokesman david simpson said the 
department has seized six vehicles since the bill became law in 
december and hasnt had any problems 
public nuisance laws in wisconsin allow the court to seize and 
sell any personal property involved with prostitution creating the 
possibility an entire family could be left homeless if one person 
engaged in sex for pay said eunice edgar executive director of 
the wisconsin aclu 
obviously we see some problems with that ms edgar said 
im not sure how the seizure of vehicles would apply i think 
theres a doublewhammy for women who are married to philanderers 
first theyre subjected to humiliation and then they lose the 
family car and cant go to work she said 
ms edgar said the wisconsin aclu lawyers would review the bill 
