naacp leaders said monday after a meeting with 
president bush there may be some movements in the effort to 
find the terrorists responsible for mail bombings in the south 
their assessment came as fbi agents searched a warehouse in 
enterprise ala in an action a spokesman said could very well 
be linked to the bombing investigation 
dr william f gibson a greenville sc dentist and chairman 
of the naacp board of directors said after meeting with bush 
attorney general dick thornburgh and fbi director william sessions 
we got indications that there are some movements in the cases i 
cant say anything further 
naacp executive director benjamin l hooks said we were 
fairly well satisfied that the federal bureau of investigation and 
the justice department were doing their best 
white house spokesman marlin fitzwater said thornburgh simply 
said that we were making progress that he was hopeful but he 
could not give any specifics at that point 
mail bombs claimed the lives of a federal appeals judge in 
alabama and a savannah ga civil rights lawyers in november 
other bombs were mailed to the federal courthouse in atlanta and 
the naacp branch office in jacksonville fla but were intercepted 
before exploding 
among the 17 naacp officials at the white house meeting were 
willye dennis head of the jacksonville office and erl shinhoster 
director of its atlanta regional office where a tear gas bomb 
exploded last aug 21 
hooks who also met with bush on jan 9 to discuss the attacks 
said we are concerned about the climate that has caused race 
relations to deteriorate and increased acts of violence 
he suggested that last weeks arrest of district of columbia 
mayor marion barry on cocaine charges not discussed at the white 
house meeting may be part of a pattern of undue harassment of 
black elected officials and part of the rising tide of racism in 
this nation 
hooks said the ku klux klan and skinheads have picketed the 
naacps national headquarters in baltimore twice in recent weeks 
were concerned about the mood the kind of relationships that 
are developing schisms between blacks and whites in america said 
gibson 
we encouraged the president to use his office to get the 
word over that we feel that there needs to be more relations and 
negotiations and discussions between black america and white 
america said gibson 
they said they asked bush and thornburgh to use the justice 
departments community relations service and a revised us 
commission on civil rights to promote such a dialogue bush was 
amicable toward those steps gibson said 
hooks said they did not discuss with the president the widely 
publicized barry arrest in a fbi sting operation in a washington 
hotel last thursday 
but hooks said there is no question about the fact that we at 
the naacp across the past few years have felt that there has been 
undue emphasis on harassing black elected officials 
thornburgh asked later about the harassment charge said if 
that were the case it would be intolerable it is not the case 
hooks said newspaper accounts made it sound like the search 
had finally paid off we spent all of these years trying to find 
him with a grain of cocaine and by god we did it didnt we 
we havent found all the people whove stolen all the money 
from the savings and loan associations and are driving rolls royces 
and jaguars so obviously many of us in the black community will 
have some peculiar feelings as we go further 
hooks was asked if he objected to bringing lawbreakers to 
justice 
no i think you ought to bring everybody to justice for 
violating the law that would have meant most of us here would be 
arrested for speeding spitting on the sidewalk or something if we 
can afford to do it lets do it 
bush has said nothing of the barry arrest except that it was 
very sad 
