more than 500 have been wounded in the conflicts 
tass said the 12 new deaths occurred when armenian militants 
fired on an azerbaijani village in the volchy vorota border area 
azerbaijani activists told a moscow news conference monday that 
3700 died when soviet troops entered baku tass said but it 
emphasized this was an unconfirmed figure 
an emergency overnight session of the azerbaijani supreme soviet 
legislature demanded full withdrawal of soviet troops from the 
republic with the exception of border districts with armenia said 
baku lawyer viliyad mamedov who attended the 11hour overnight 
session 
lawmakers also demanded lifting of the curfew and state of 
emergency in baku and other areas of azerbaijan which moscow 
imposed without the approval of azerbaijani authorities mamedov 
said in a telephone interview 
if those demands are not met mamedov said the legislature will 
consider voting to secede from the soviet union 
at mondays mass rally in baku demonstrators carried posters 
reading gorbachev is the butcher of the azerbaijani people 
and azerbaijanis will not succumb to tanks said shain gajiyev 
a baku journalist 
witnesses said throngs of mourners numbering as many as 2 
million bore coffins of azerbaijanis killed in the weekend assault 
down the narrow streets and major thoroughfares to lenin square 
now renamed freedom square in honor of the azerbaijani nationalist 
cause 
the mourners wearing black and carrying blackbordered 
portraits of some of the victims then buried the victims at kirov 
park overlooking the caspian sea 
all the people of azerbaijan and baku are in tears and 
mourning official baku radio said in a broadcast monitored by 
the bbc in london 
soviet troops and police did not interfere in the funeral said 
leila yunusov a spokeswoman for the social democratic group an 
informal azerbaijani political organization 
foreign reporters were barred from the region so it was 
difficult to determine the exact death toll or reconcile 
conflicting information 
military officials said no one had been killed in baku the last 
two days and residents said the soviet troops seemed to have the 
city under control no armed clashes with troops were reported 
monday gajiyev said although scattered gunfire was heard 
conflicting reports came from the sovietiranian border where 
azerbaijanis have torn down many barriers the government newspaper 
izvestia said 40000 azerbaijanis crossed into iran on sunday 
evening alone but iranian media said soviet troops clamped down on 
the border and were not letting azerbaijanis out 
interfax an affiliate of radio moscow said unidentified 
extremists threatened russian residents of baku with violence 
unless they left and threatened to blow up oil tankers in bakus 
harbor unless troops were withdrawn 
soviet tv on monday evening suggested the government launch 
negotiations with the azerbaijani peoples front the nationalist 
organization behind much of the unrest the evening news program 
said since the peoples front controls some areas of azerbaijan it 
is the logical partner for peace talks 
it was not clear whether the peoples front and armenian 
activists participated in the negotiations in the armenian town of 
yeraskh 
highranking armenian and azerbaijani communist party and 
government officials also agreed to repair disrupted communications 
lines 
in a statement issued monday peoples fronts from the soviet 
baltic republics of lithuania latvia and estonia commiserated with 
the azerbaijanis and said moscow with its centralized policies 
was to blame for provoking the conflict they offered riga the 
latvian capital as a site for peace talks 
armenias popular movements condemned moscow for the baku 
deaths when armenians demanded protection for themselves and 
punishment for azerbaijani extremists who victimized them they 
did not mean a deployment of the soviet army in a largescale 
bloody action but the use of civilized methods proper to a 
lawbased state the armenian board of national movements said 
the statement read over the phone by activist rafael popayan 
from yerevan the armenian capital said innocent blood is being 
shed and that cannot leave the armenian people indifferent 
at a protest march by 2000 azerbaijanis in moscow on monday 
one demonstrator carried a sign reading comrades in baku more 
than 9000 people were killed 
a gathering monday in the azerbaijani town of pushkino to mourn 
those slain ended in mass rioting tass said 
the explosion into violence of the longstanding hostility 
between armenia and azerbaijan is considered one of the worst 
crises gorbachev has faced in his nearly fiveyear tenure as soviet 
leader 
moscow sent thousands of troops and other forces to baku after 
fighting flared between the moslem azerbaijanis and mainly 
christian armenians this month the neighboring republics are 
locked in a decadesold dispute over the region of 
nagornokarabakh which is inside azerbaijan but populated mainly 
by armenians 
the total number of soviet forces combating the violence in 
armenia and azerbaijan is reported to be 29000 including troops 
police cadets and interior ministry forces the number of 
militants is reported in the thousands 
violence began jan 13 with antiarmenian rioting in baku that 
killed 67 people by official count and sent thousands of armenians 
fleeing from their homes in panic it escalated into open warfare 
elsewhere in azerbaijan 
