a former armored car guard who gambled away 
651000 stolen from his truck during two years on the lam agreed 
monday to return to philadelphia for trial 
edward leigh hunt jr told reporters he had spent his two years 
as a fugitive living in hollywood a block from the chinese 
theater and consumed much of the time studying spanish because 
i love languages 
im very glad the whole thing is over he said 
the 26yearold hunt handcuffed and wearing blue jail 
coveralls waived extradition on interstate theft charges 
hunt wouldnt explain details of a gambling system he has said 
he devised in an effort to make a profit on the money taken jan 
20 1988 from a truck belonging to the brooks armored car co in 
philadelphia 
i stole the money because i thought i could quadruple it 
