for the fourth time in six 
months argentina has a new central bank president 
enrique folcini was appointed to the post monday following the 
resignation of rodolfo rossi who lasted five weeks 
analysts said rossi was forced out by private banks troubled by 
the governments decision jan 1 to convert several billion dollars 
of shortterm certificates of deposits to 10year bonds in a bid to 
stabilize the economy 
that move curtailed currency speculation that was devaluing the 
austral daily and reduced skyhigh 600percentamonth interest 
rates by abruptly restricting the money supply 
however private banks said their reserves held by the central 
bank were not enough to cover the new bonds and wrangled with 
economy ministry officials to expand use of the bonds something 
rossi opposed 
