<TEXT>
fruit exports to the united states from 
the central aconcagua valley resumed monday five days after the 
discovery of mediterranean fruit flies in the area prompted a 
regional quarantine 
authorities said the problem is now considered under control 
and no new findings of flies were reported after fruit was 
fumigated and trees were sprayed with pesticide in the valley 50 
miles northeast of the capital santiago 
mondays shipment from the aconcagua valley was the first since 
authorities reported wednesday that at least 12 mediterranean fruit 
flies the first since 1978 were found in a residential 
neighborhood of los andes 
ronald bown president of the fruit exporters association said 
47000 crates of grapes and other fruit from the valley were loaded 
monday in the neighboring port of valparaiso for shipment to the 
united states 
the aconcagua area fruit was fumigated and stored in cold 
chambers in the boat separated from 300000 crates of fruit from 
other regions in the country the lowtemperature storage for 
periods of three to four days is a common procedure to fight the 
fly and its larvae which are harmless to humans 
experts from the united states department of agriculture 
supervised the shipment bown said 
jorge prado president of the national agriculture society an 
organization of chiles largest private farmers said the main 
problem in the aconcagua valley now is the lack of enough 
fumigation capacity and cold storage facilities 
grapes peaches nectarines and kiwis are grown in the aconcagua 
area about 16 million crates are expected to be harvested this 
year in the valley virtually all for export to the united states 
japan and western europe 
last year chiles fruit exporters suffered a major blow when 
two grapes laced with cyanide were found in a chilean shipment in 
philadelphia 
the finding prompted the us food and drug administration to 
temporarily ban the sale of chilean fruit in the united states 
resulting losses were estimated at 300 million 
fruit exports have boomed in recent years earning about 900 
million annually for chile which as latin americas fourth largest 
foreign debt 
