winners such as jerome robbins broadway and the heidi 
chronicles which also won a pulitzer prize has been the most 
successful and visible company 
but it isnt the only japanese concern to take a chance on the 
broadway lottery among the foreign investors in new york theater 
production have been tv asahi and the tokyo broadcasting system as 
well as haruki kadokawa owner of kadokawa publishing not all of 
their investments were successful some lost money 
win or lose japanese participation in broadway production is 
growing of the 18 shows that opened on broadway between september 
and the end of 1989 seven productions gypsy city of 
angels a few good men the circle tru the secret 
rapture and 3 penny opera had japanese financial backing 
five by suntory 
i think it flows with all of the investments being made out of 
