bloodshed it urged china to ease its hardline stance toward 
dissent and after martial law was lifted a team of japanese 
officials went to china to reopen negotiations on the loans 
chinas economy has been plagued in recent years by 
overproduction of some items scarcities of many resources 
widespread construction of unnecessary or unaffordable buildings 
and facilities and soaring inflation 
we have a few economic problems at the moment but they are 
problems that go along with progress and we will overcome them 
zou said if you look at the overheated tempo of industrial 
growth over a few years it has come down to a more reasonable 
level 
