researcher at the sociology faculty of leiden state university 
the national unlisted average in this country of 146 million is 
10 percent of 65 million telephones according to fred lemmerink 
a spokesman for ptt telecom the national phone company 
opting for an unlisted number is an act of defiance of 
escaping from the ubiquitous eye of the government engbersen 
said in a monday interview 
