<TEXT>
the government today filed preliminary 
charges against a swedish arms manufacturer accusing the company 
of paying 50 million in kickbacks to seal a 1986 arms deal 
investigators said former indian prime minister rajiv gandhi 
would be among those questioned 
gandhi has said repeatedly that he did not gain personally from 
the deal and that no indians received kickbacks or commissions in 
the contract with the company ab bofors 
bofors spokesman johnny ericsson said in stockholm sweden that 
the company would have no comment 
rajendra shekhar director of the central bureau of 
investigation told reporters the preliminary charges would form 
the launching pad for an investigation 
the charges identify three people as the accused in the 
case gopichand hinduja a londonbased indian industrialist 
martin ardbo who was president of bofors when the deal was signed 
and win chadha the bofors agent in new delhi 
shekhar said several others including top indian officials 
also were involved but he refused to identify them 
the legal action was the first step by new prime minister vp 
singh toward fulfilling his election campaign promise to root out 
corruption which he said flourished under gandhi 
gandhis government signed the 1986 contract with bofors and 
agreed to pay 14 billion for 410 155mm howitzers but the 
following year charges surfaced in swedish and indian news media of 
kickbacks in the deal 
shekhar said at least 50 million was paid through swiss banks 
to clinch the sale 
newspaper reports have claimed that much of the money was paid 
to intermediaries including people close to gandhi and in the 
ruling circles of his congress party 
the corruption charges dogged gandhi through the rest of his 
tenure giving singh a powerful weapon in last novembers national 
election 
although gandhi outpolled singh in the balloting he could not 
muster a majority of seats in parliament and singh formed a 
minority government with support from other parties 
the preliminary charges filed before a district judge in new 
delhi listed these alleged offenses criminal conspiracy cheating 
and dishonestly inducing delivery of property forgery forgery for 
the purpose of cheating criminal breach of trust and abuse of 
official position by public servants 
the charges carry penalties that include unspecified fines and 
prison terms 
