<TEXT>
the supreme court agreed on monday to resolve 
a procedural dispute over denied social security disability 
benefits 
the court said it will review the case of a new jersey widow 
whose 1983 application for disability benefits was denied by the 
department of health and human services 
but the courts decision expected by july will not determine 
whether marilyn finkelstein 59 is entitled to the benefits 
instead the justices will decide whether a federal trial 
judges order that hhs officials reconsider her application may be 
appealed by hhs to a federal appeals court before any such 
reconsideration 
mrs finkelstein sued and a federal judge in newark ruled that 
hhs had used the wrong standard in determining her eligibility for 
disability benefits 
the 3rd us circuit court of appeals dismissed the governments 
ensuing appeal saying the trial judges order was not a final 
decision that could be appealed immediately 
the government then filed the appeal acted on today 
the case is sullivan vs finkelstein 89504 
</TEXT>
