investment banker jeffrey beck an adviser on 
some of the biggest us corporate takeovers ever lied about his 
past fabricating stories about his background and military service 
and claiming to work for the cia according to a published report 
monday 
beck who cultivated a colorful image that included the nickname 
mad dog rose to stardom on wall street even though one of his 
tales helped kill a planned billiondollar buyout of northwest 
industries inc in 1985 the wall street journal reported 
beck 43 a member of drexel burnham lambert incs mergers and 
acquisitions department allegedly told friends and colleagues over 
the years that he was a decorated veteran of the armys special 
