phillips petroleum co received a 92 
million settlement monday from the government of iran and the 
national iranian oil co for a 1981 claim for the expropriation of 
phillips interest in two offshore oil fields 
phillips filed the claim with the iranus claims tribunal 
which in june awarded phillips about 110 million for expropriation 
of the companys onesixth interest in the oil fields 
iran followed with counterclaims against phillips which the 
tribunal did not dispose of because of lack of jurisdiction 
regarding oil received by phillips under the purchase contract 
the 92 million settlement ends all claims and counterclaims 
between iran and phillips said phillips spokesman george minter 
phillips received a net payment monday of 91 million because of 
a statutory fee of 1 million deducted by the us treasury 
department 
