amoco corp said monday its fourthquarter earnings fell 15 
percent because of special onetime gains in the previous year 
while arco said higher oil prices helped its quarterly earnings 
rise 3 percent and amerada hess corp posted a 7 percent rise in 
profits as exploration and production earnings surged 
for the three months ended dec 31 chicagobased amoco earned 
319 million or 62 cents a share down from 375 million or 72 
cents a share in the comparable 1988 period revenue rose 10 
percent to 68 billion from 62 billion 
